Question: Which of the following is a typical declaration of a triply linked list in C?
Choices:
a) struct node { int data; struct node *previous; struct node *top; };
b) struct node { int data; struct node *next; struct node *top; };
c) struct node { int data; struct node *next; struct node *previous; struct node *top; };
d) struct node { int data; struct node *next; struct node *previous; };
Answer: c

