Question: Select the code snippet which performs in-order traversal.
Choices:
a) public void inorder(Tree root) {
	System.out.println(root.data);
	inorder(root.left);
	inorder(root.right);
}
b) public void inorder(Tree root) {
	inorder(root.left);
	System.out.println(root.data);
	inorder(root.right);
}
c) public void inorder(Tree root) {
	System.out.println(root.data);
	inorder(root.right);
	inorder(root.left);
}
d) public void inorder(Tree root) {
	inorder(root.right);
	inorder(root.left);
	System.out.println(root.data);
}
Answer: b

Question: What must be the missing logic in place of missing lines for finding sum of nodes of binary tree in alternate levels?
Choices:
a) i=i+pow(2,currentlevel);
currentlevel=currentlevel+2;
j=1;
b) i=i+pow(2,currentlevel);
currentlevel=currentlevel+2;
j=0;
c) i=i-pow(2,currentlevel);
currentlevel=currentlevel+2;
j=1;
d) i=i+pow(2,currentlevel);
currentlevel=currentlevel+1;
j=1;
